    "body": "![medium](https://www.gstatic.com/codereviewagent/medium-priority.svg)\n\nYou have added `sqlalchemy[asyncio]` but are using `psycopg2-binary` as the PostgreSQL driver. `psycopg2` is a synchronous driver and does not support asyncio. If you plan to use asynchronous database operations with SQLAlchemy, you should use an async-compatible driver like `asyncpg`. If you intend to use synchronous operations, you can remove the `[asyncio]` extra from `sqlalchemy`.\n\nAdditionally, the `psycopg2-binary` package is discouraged for production use by its maintainers; `psycopg2` (built from source) is preferred for production environments.",
